<br>
While both Casting Mastery and MC will effectively reduce your downtime, only Casting Mastery can increase the number of nukes you can fire on a full tank of mana.<br>
<br>
For this reason, when in doubt I plan to stick to Mastery. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urombusmindspire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Forum Sorcerer</font></td></tr></table><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>NOT Rhombus!</font></td></tr></table></span><br>  Posts: 3064<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/25/02 4:07 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.tritonguild.com/rombus/sidepic.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Luclin Abilities Analysis</span><hr size=1> IMO Fury &gt; Mastery.  The improvements seen with Mastery aren't as dramatic as I was expecting and Fury really does help quite a bit.  It's a personal choice though. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
